OL,5, Home Secretary James Cleverly has      
OL,6, apologised for making an "ironic joke" 
OL,7, about spiking his wife's drink at a    
OL,8, Downing Street reception.              
OL,10,FHe reportedly said the ideal spouse was
OL,11,F"someone who is always mildly sedated  
OL,12,Fso she can never realise there are     
OL,13,Fbetter men out there".                 
OL,15,FAccording to the Sunday Mirror, he also
OL,16,Fmentioned Rohypnol - a so-called "date 
OL,17,Frape" drug.                            
OL,19,FSenior Labour party figures have       
OL,20,Fdescribed the comments as "appalling". 
